Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep football roundup: Royals fall in 7-2A semifinals TIMES STAFF REPORT 6:45 p.m. CDT October 17, 2015 Royalton (Photo: Times graphic) 
EVELETH â€” Top-seeded Eveleth-Gilbert scored once in the third quarter and once in the fourth to top No. 4 Royalton 14-0 in the Section 7-2A playoffs Saturday afternoon. 
Eveleth-Gilbert quarterback Max Roberts ran for one touchdown and threw for another to lead the Golden Bears (8-1). He finished with 105 yards rushing and 44 yards passing in the game. 
Austin Zapzalka ran for 79 yards and Matt Daleidan ran for 45 yards for Royalton. Ryan Fussy threw for 27 yards for the Royals. 
Royalton finished its season 6-4 overall.
